H0.text: Which member of the earwig family is also known as a fishmoth. Earwig Beetle

H1.text: Which member of the earwig family is also known as a fishmoth. Silverfish

H2.text: Which member of the earwig family is also known as a fishmoth. Tachycines

H3.text: Which member of the earwig family is also known as a fishmoth. Fishmoth

A4.text: The silverfish (Lepisma saccharinum) is a species of small, primitive, wingless insect in the order Zygentoma.

A5.text: The Zygentoma include the silverfishes or fishmoths, and the firebrats.

A6.text: Tachycines is a genus of camel crickets in the subfamily Aemodogryllinae and tribe Aemodogryllini.
